File Destruction
-----------------


-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
from: https://www.hackers-arise.com/post/2017/10/17/Mr-Robot-Hacks-Season-3-How-Elliot-Covered-his-Tracks
Deleted files can still be recovered; the Kali Linux tool `shred` overwrites files so that they cannot be recovered:

$ shred --help

$ shred [OPTION]... [FILE]...

$ shred -f -n 5 secret_plan
# -f = force [change permissions to allow writing if necessary]
# -n 5 = overwrite 5 times [default is 3 times]
# secret_plan = name of file targeted for destruction; note using * [wildcard] will shred all files

